  "body": "**ðŸ§ Motivation**\r\nThe Pragma version creates a problem in the compilation processes.\r\n\r\n**ðŸ“ Details**\r\nAs compiling and deploying both require to have the .sol files to have the exact `pragma` editions, OpenZeppelin did a very decent job of keeping all of the files with a version of `^0.8.0`, however, after installing the contracts with ` npm install @openzeppelin/contracts` and trying to compile the project source code, I have noticed that `Address.sol` is using `pragma version ^0.8.1`, which creates an obstacle in the compilation process. I wondered if `Address.sol` had any specific purpose for using `^0.8.1` instead of `^0.8.0`? If not, then bringing it back to the `^0.8.0` would not be a good idea for a faster and smoother dev experience?\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/utils/Address.sol#L4",
