    "body": ">As compiling and deploying both require to have the .sol files to have the exact pragma editions\r\n\r\nThis is not true. Files can have different pragmas. You need to use a compiler version that satisfies all pragmas. The latest 0.8 release will work. If you are only using files with `^0.8.0` and `^0.8.1` then you can use 0.8.1 or any later version.\r\n\r\nThe file has pragma `^0.8.1` because it needs a feature of the language that is only available in 0.8.1, it will not be possible to compile it with 0.8.0.",
